<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="527" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1127,220,1491]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,280,1340,1363]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name refers to ‘Putkarôt’, the name by which the Xikrin call themselves, in honor of the indigenous people present in the area of origin of the 
<typeStatus box="[961,1058,1372,1395]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">holotype</typeStatus>
. It is a noun in the nominative singular standing in apposition.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1127,220,1491]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,436,1436,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
So far 
<taxonomicName authority="Guimarães &amp; Ferreira-Jr, 2017" authorityName="Guimarães &amp; Ferreira-Jr" authorityYear="2017" box="[523,760,1436,1459]" class="Insecta" family="Noteridae" genus="Canthysellus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="putkarot" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[523,760,1436,1459]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Canthysellus putkarot</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[770,856,1436,1459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="527" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is known only from the Floresta Nacional de Carajás, Parauapebas Municipality in the Brazilian state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1012,1063,1468,1491]" country="Suriname" name="Para" pageId="6" pageNumber="527">Pará</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
